# Agent protocol

You are working inside a project tracked in `sdlc-portfolio-manager` (a local
control plane that the human you're working for runs on this machine). The
`pc` CLI is on your PATH and talks to the manager at `http://localhost:3737`
by default. Use it.

## The loop

Every time you start a chunk of work, follow this protocol:

1. **Claim work** ‚Äî run `pc next` (optionally with `--type` / `--label`).
   - If a `ready` item exists, the CLI prints `id`, `title`, `type`, status,
     assignee, and description on stdout in `tab\separated` lines and exits 0.
   - If nothing is ready, exit code is 2 ‚Äî go back to the human or stop.
2. **Work the item** ‚Äî read the description, look at the parent if there is
   one, check the acceptance criteria.
3. **If you're stuck or need a decision** ‚Äî file a HITL question:
   ```
   pc ask <item-id> "Should I use OAuth or magic links?" --addressed-to bryce
   ```
   The work item flips to `needs-human` automatically. Either:
   - exit and come back later (`pc check-answer <q-id> <item-id>` from your
     next session ‚Äî exits 5 until answered), OR
   - block with `pc ask <id> "‚Ä¶" --wait 600` to wait up to 10 minutes.
4. **Record evidence as you go** ‚Äî when you implement something that satisfies
   an acceptance criterion, post evidence so the `user-story-acceptance`
   validation gate matches it:
   ```
   pc comment <item-id> --kind evidence --criterion AC-1 \
     "Implemented in src/foo.ts:42; covered by foo.test.ts"
   ```
5. **Move to in_review** ‚Äî `pc done <item-id>`. This auto-triggers the four
   validation gates (`quality`, `security`, `bugs`, `user-story-acceptance`).
6. **Verify gates** ‚Äî `pc validation-status <item-id>` to see results. Failing
   gates need to be fixed before ship.
7. **Ship** ‚Äî `pc ship <item-id>`. The CLI exits 1 with a structured error if
   any gate is still failing. Don't pass `--override-reason` unless the human
   has explicitly approved it.

## Discipline

- **Never invent work.** If you find a bug or want to file a follow-up, use
  `pc file bug "<short title>"` (description on stdin). Don't leave TODO
  comments scattered in the code ‚Äî they vanish.
- **Use the structure.** When you have a chunky problem, file an `epic` with
  child `story` items. Use `--parent <epic-id>` when filing children.
- **Respect needs-human.** If you flip an item to `needs-human` via a
  question, don't claim other work on that item until the question resolves.
- **Don't override gates silently.** `pc ship --override-reason "‚Ä¶"` is a
  break-glass for the human, not for agents.

## Config

- `PC_API_URL` ‚Äî default `http://localhost:3737`
- `PC_AGENT` ‚Äî your agent name (default `cursor-bg`). Set this so the human
  can see who's working what.
- `PC_PROJECT` ‚Äî the project slug for this repo. The human should set this
  once per project. If unset, `pc` falls back to repo-path lookup.

If `pc` ever returns a 404 like "no project with slug X", the human needs to
either set `PC_PROJECT` or bind the project's `target_repo_path` to this
folder via the web UI's Project ‚Üí Settings page.
